---
import SidebarLayout from '../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import WorkCard from '../../components/WorkCard.astro';

const context = [
  { label: 'ROLE', value: 'Lead Product Designer' },
  { label: 'PLATFORM', value: 'iOS & Android by Flutter' },
  { label: 'DURATION', value: '6 month' },
  { label: 'DOMAIN', value: 'Fintech / Crypto', domain: true },
];
const results = [
  { value: '156', label: 'Screens & states delivered' },
  { value: '90%', label: 'Bugs caught pre-production' },
  { value: '40%', label: 'faster concept-to-release cycle' },
  { value: '1', label: 'Ready to launch Crypto-bank' },
];

const nextCase = {
  href: '/cases/livematch',
  title: 'Live Match Pages Redesign',
  description: 'How a technical refactoring initiative evolved into a new way to present sports statistics',
  imageSrc: '/works/sports-matches.png',
  layout: 'full' as const,
  statValue: 'Top 3',
  statLabel: 'SEO ranking',
  statRows: [
    { width: 65, color: '#fc5b04', label: '+34% Time on Page per Session' },
    { width: 52, color: '#4a9000', label: '+48% Average Scroll Depth' },
    { width: 91, color: '#464c63', label: '+73% Total Live Page Views' },
  ],
};
---

<SidebarLayout title="Yollet — Eugen Trapeznikov" centered whiteContent backHref="/">

  <main class="yl">

    <!-- ─── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-hero">
      <div class="yl-hero__head">
        <h1 class="yl-h1">Yollet - exchanger without p2p</h1>
        <p class="yl-subtitle">The product combines crypto asset management with familiar banking experiences, built on a compliant and legally structured infrastructure. Its mission is to provide users with a convenient, secure, and transparent way to store, exchange, and spend cryptocurrency</p>
      </div>
      <div class="yl-hero__cards">
        <div class="card yl-card">
          <span class="yl-h-sm">Context</span>
          <div class="yl-ctx-list">
            {context.map((c) => (
              <div class="yl-ctx-item">
                <span class="yl-ctx-label">{c.label}</span>
                <span class={`yl-ctx-value${c.domain ? ' yl-ctx-value--domain' : ''}`}>{c.value}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card yl-card yl-stat-card">
          <span class="yl-h-sm">Results</span>
          <div class="yl-stat-list">
            {results.map((r) => (
              <div class="yl-stat">
                <span class="yl-stat-value">{r.value}</span>
                <span class="yl-stat-label">{r.label}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── SUMMARY ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-lg">Summary</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>When I joined the team, the product already had an early MVP and a basic UI-kit in place. I was brought in to introduce more structure to the design process and shorten the path from idea to release.</p>
          <p>My responsibilities included:</p>
          <ul class="yl-list">
            <li>Auditing the existing product design and interface system.</li>
            <li>Designing key user flows, including exchange, swap, KYC, and onboarding.</li>
            <li>Defining the UX strategy and long-term product vision.</li>
            <li>Establishing collaboration processes with engineering teams, including design reviews and handoff workflows, to reduce release errors and improve delivery speed.</li>
            <li>Conducting user research. To support this, a beta version of the product was launched, allowing us to gather feedback from the first users</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/main-screen.png" alt="Yollet main screen" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <!-- ─── AUDIT ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-sm">Product Audit &amp; Core User Flows</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>I approached the audit systematically by reviewing every user flow from a UI perspective, without challenging the underlying product logic. Each screen was evaluated using a simple traffic-light framework:</p>
          <p>🟢 No critical issues.<br />🟡 Issues that could be resolved through visual or stylistic improvements without changing the layout.<br />🔴 Issues requiring changes to layouts, components, or entire user flows.</p>
          <p>I documented usability issues and opportunities across screens, from visual inconsistencies to broader product hypotheses.</p>
          <p>For example, in the wallet creation flow, the seed phrase and multiple confirmations increased anxiety and drop-offs, highlighting the need to simplify the UI and reduce user friction during onboarding</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="yl-imgcard">
        <img src="/cases/yollet/legend.png" alt="Traffic-light audit legend" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── DESIGNING KEY USER FLOWS ─────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-sm">Designing Key User Flows</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>The audit provided the team with a shared understanding of the product's key issues and helped align priorities for future improvements. Based on these findings, I moved on to designing the new core user flows and defining the future product experience.</p>
          <p>In parallel, I worked on establishing design operations: introducing design reviews, improving developer handoff processes, and building a design system to create consistency across the product and increase the speed and quality of releases</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="yl-screens">
        <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/buy-sell.png" alt="Buy / Sell flow" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/tokens-management.png" alt="Token management flow" loading="lazy" />
        <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/wallet-setup.png" alt="Wallet setup flow" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── DESIGN SYSTEM ────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-sm">Design System: a Single Source of Truth</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>I turned fragmentation into a structured system: Figma as the source of truth, Storybook for coded components, and a shared naming convention across both. I also introduced a two-level token system, typographic and colour scale.</p>
          <p>Designers and engineers aligned on a shared language, eliminating ad-hoc component creation. Hardcoded values were replaced with design tokens, variables, and system components, ensuring consistency across both design and code.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/design-system.png" alt="Design system components" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <!-- ─── DESIGN PROCESS & REVIEWS ──────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-sm">Design Process &amp; Design Reviews</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>I introduced a structured design review format, including screen context, side-by-side comparison of live vs. design, numbered annotated issues, and a separate stream for proposed improvements. I also established a repeatable end-to-end design process — from brief to product analytics.</p>
          <p>This fundamentally changed the way design supported development: we moved from minimal design involvement to a pixel-perfect, system-driven workflow with formal design reviews and a shared design system, significantly reducing implementation issues. The introduction of staging environments helped catch up to 90% of bugs before release.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/design-review.png" alt="Design review format" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <!-- ─── UX STRATEGY ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-sm">UX Strategy &amp; Information Architecture</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>I ran a series of workshops with the founders and translated the outcomes into a structured design brief, feature prioritization, and a product map. A key decision was defining the portfolio as the new home screen, with the wallet as the core experience and a flexible structure designed to accommodate future features.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/strategy.png" alt="Product map and concepts" loading="lazy" />
      <img class="yl-media" src="/cases/yollet/concepts.png" alt="Exploring a new product approach" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <!-- ─── OVERALL ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="yl-sec">
      <div class="yl-head2">
        <h2 class="yl-h-lg">Overall</h2>
        <div class="yl-text">
          <p>A structured design system, streamlined processes, and a shared UX strategy and product vision were established in close alignment with founders and stakeholders — spanning from the MVP wallet to a broader crypto-banking roadmap.</p>
          <p>The work received positive feedback from both investors and early users.</p>
          <p>Most importantly, the product was successfully prepared for market launch, and the first beta users were onboarded. This achievement reflects a collective effort of the team, who delivered under tight timelines driven by strong ownership and execution quality.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="yl-stats-grid">
        {results.map((r, i) => (
          <div class={`yl-stat-block${i === results.length - 1 ? ' yl-stat-block--accent' : ''}`}>
            <span class="yl-stat-value">{r.value}</span>
            <span class="yl-stat-label">{r.label}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── NEXT CASE ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="yl-divider"></div>
    <section class="yl-next">
      <h2 class="yl-h-lg">Next work</h2>
      <WorkCard {...nextCase} bordered />
    </section>

  </main>

</SidebarLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Page column: 1000px, left-aligned, 80px between blocks ── */
  .yl {
    max-width: 1000px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 80px;
  }
  .card { background: var(--bg-surface); border-radius: 20px; }

  .yl-sec { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 32px; }
  .yl-screens { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }

  /* Section header: title left / text right */
  .yl-head2 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; }

  /* ── Hero (still stacked: title above subtitle) ─────────── */
  .yl-hero { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .yl-hero__head { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 64px; }

  .yl-h1 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-5xl);      /* 32px */
    line-height: 40px;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    color: var(--content-primary);
  }
  .yl-subtitle { font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 24px; color: var(--content-secondary); max-width: 800px; }

  .yl-hero__cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; }

  /* ── Typography ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .yl-h-lg {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-5xl);      /* 32px */
    line-height: 40px;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    color: var(--content-primary);
  }
  .yl-h-sm {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);      /* 22px */
    line-height: 32px;
    color: var(--content-primary);
  }
  .yl-text { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
  .yl-text p { font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 24px; color: var(--content-secondary); }
  .yl-list {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px;
    padding-left: 24px; list-style: disc;
    font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 24px; color: var(--content-secondary);
  }

  /* ── Media (images already carry their own light-gray card fill) ── */
  .yl-media { width: 100%; display: block; }

  /* Legend image hasn't been re-exported with a gray fill yet — wrap it ourselves */
  .yl-imgcard { background: var(--bg-surface); border-radius: 16px; padding: 32px 64px; display: flex; justify-content: center; }
  .yl-imgcard img { width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; display: block; }

  /* ── Context / Results cards (hero) ─────────────────────── */
  .yl-card { padding: 32px 64px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 32px; }
  .yl-ctx-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 32px; }
  .yl-ctx-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
  .yl-ctx-label { font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 24px; color: var(--content-secondary); }
  .yl-ctx-value { font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: 24px; color: var(--content-primary); }
  .yl-ctx-value--domain { color: #6b5fd4; }

  .yl-stat-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }
  .yl-stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px);
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease-out, transform 0.5s ease-out;
  }
  .yl-stat-value {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);      /* 26px */
    line-height: 40px;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    color: var(--content-primary);
  }
  .yl-stat-label { font-size: var(--text-md); line-height: 20px; color: var(--content-secondary); }
  .yl-stat-card.in-view .yl-stat { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
  .yl-stat-card.in-view .yl-stat:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0.05s; }
  .yl-stat-card.in-view .yl-stat:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.15s; }
  .yl-stat-card.in-view .yl-stat:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.25s; }
  .yl-stat-card.in-view .yl-stat:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 0.35s; }

  /* ── Overall: 2×2 stat grid, last block accent-highlighted ── */
  .yl-stats-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .yl-stat-block {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 32px 64px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px);
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease-out, transform 0.5s ease-out;
  }
  .yl-stat-block .yl-stat-value { line-height: 1; }
  .yl-stat-block--accent { background: var(--domain-fintech); }
  .yl-stat-block--accent .yl-stat-value,
  .yl-stat-block--accent .yl-stat-label { color: var(--always-white); }
  .yl-stats-grid.in-view .yl-stat-block { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
  .yl-stats-grid.in-view .yl-stat-block:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0.05s; }
  .yl-stats-grid.in-view .yl-stat-block:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.15s; }
  .yl-stats-grid.in-view .yl-stat-block:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.25s; }
  .yl-stats-grid.in-view .yl-stat-block:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 0.35s; }

  /* ── Next case ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .yl-divider { height: 0.5px; background: var(--border-default); }
  .yl-next { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }

  /* ── Responsive ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .yl { gap: 56px; max-width: 100%; }
    .yl-hero__head { margin-bottom: 40px; }
    .yl-hero__cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .yl-head2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 12px; }
    .yl-card { padding: 24px; }
    .yl-imgcard { padding: 20px; }
    .yl-stats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .yl-stat-block { padding: 24px; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const cards = document.querySelectorAll('.yl-stat-card, .yl-stats-grid');
  const obs = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach((e) => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        e.target.classList.add('in-view');
        obs.unobserve(e.target);
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.2 });
  cards.forEach((c) => obs.observe(c));
</script>
